{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, the equivalence of (2.17) to the NLSM at the quantum level has been discussed previously in [22], where it is stated that the equivalence can be trusted when the path integral is dominated by large Φ contributions.",
    "We are not aware of any substantive work relating the approach of [50] to the NLSM at the quantum level.",
    "However, if a formal limit of Φ → ∞ is taken and the interaction term of (2.17) is dropped, then this theory appears to be qualitatively different -it is not clear how such a theory would relate to the NLSM on AdS 3.",
    "40 For a string in flat spacetime, it is the x µ, conjugate to the zero mode α µ 0 + αµ 0 of ∂X µ (z) + ∂X µ (z) that provides a coordinate for spacetime.",
    "Similarly, on a torus, conjugates of both momentum and winding zero modes provide coordinates on the doubled target space geometry."
  ]
}